tvshowdetails.label: Lost
tvshowdetails.plot: After their plane, Oceanic Air flight 815, tore apart whilst thousands of miles off course, the survivors find themselves on a mysterious deserted island where they soon find out they are not alone.
tvshowdetails.title: Lost

4.label: 4x01. The Beginning of the End
4.plot: They thought they had met the enemy. They thought they had seen evil. They thought wrong. As the new season begins, the survivors feel that rescue is close at hand, but they don't know whether or not to believe Charlie's final message that the people claiming to liberate them are not who they seem to be. As unlikely alliances are formed, those they thought could be trusted may turn against them, as the enemy of their enemy becomes their friend. But who can be trusted? Is rescue really as close as it seems?
4.title: The Beginning of the End

4.label: 4x02. Confirmed Dead
4.plot: The survivors begin to question the intentions of their supposed rescuers when four strangers arrive on the island.
4.title: Confirmed Dead

4.label: 4x03. The Economist
4.plot: Locke's hostage may be the key to getting off the island, so Sayid and Kate go in search of their fellow castaway in an attempt to negotiate a peaceful deal.
4.title: The Economist

4.label: 4x04. Eggtown
4.plot: Kate needs to get information out of the hostages, but it may jeopardize her standing with Locke -- as well as with Sawyer. Meanwhile in the future Kate's Court hearings take place.
4.title: Eggtown

4.label: 4x05. The Constant
4.plot: Sayid and Desmond hit a bit of turbulence on the way to the freighter, which causes Desmond to experience some unexpected side effects.
4.title: The Constant

4.label: 4x06. The Other Woman
4.plot: Juliet receives an unwelcome visit from someone from her past and is given orders to track down Charlotte and Faraday in order to stop them from completing their mission -- by any means necessary. Meanwhile, Ben offers Locke an enticing deal.
4.title: The Other Woman

4.label: 4x07. Ji Yeon
4.plot: Juliet is forced to reveal some startling news to Jin when Sun threatens to move to Locke's camp. Meanwhile, Sayid and Desmond begin to get an idea of the freighter's crew when they meet the ship's captain.
4.title: Ji Yeon

4.label: 4x08. Meet Kevin Johnson
4.plot: Sayid confronts Ben's spy on the freighter, and Ben urges daughter Alex to flee Locke's camp in order to survive an impending attack.
4.title: Meet Kevin Johnson

4.label: 4x09. The Shape of Things to Come
4.plot: Jack tries to discover the identity of a body that has washed ashore. Meanwhile, Locke's camp is attacked by Ben's adversaries.
4.title: The Shape of Things to Come

4.label: 4x10. Something Nice Back Home
4.plot: Kate and Juliet must learn to work together when Jack's health is seriously compromised, and something goes wrong as Sawyer, Claire, Aaron and Miles continue their trek away from Locke's camp and back to the beach
4.title: Something Nice Back Home

4.label: 4x11. Cabin Fever
4.plot: Locke finds out where Jacob's cabin is. Life on the freighter becomes dangerous.
4.title: Cabin Fever

5.label: 5x02. The Lie
5.plot: Hurley and Sayid are on the run from the cops after stumbling into trouble at the safehouse; the island survivors come under attack by unknown forces; and an old friend offers some shocking advice to Kate in order to ensure that "the lie" remain a secret.
5.title: The Lie

5.label: 5x03. Jughead
5.plot: Desmond looks for a woman who might be the key to helping Faraday stop the island's unpredictable movements through time; Locke finds out who has been attacking the survivors.
5.title: Jughead

5.label: 5x04. The Little Prince
5.plot: Kate discovers that someone knows the secret of Aaron's true parental lineage. Meanwhile, the dramatic shifts through time are placing the lives of the remaining island survivors in extreme peril.
5.title: The Little Prince

5.label: 5x05. This Place Is Death
5.plot: Locke shoulders the burden of ending the island's increasingly violent movements through time; Ben is stymied in his efforts to reunite the Oceanic 6 and bring them back to the island.
5.title: This Place Is Death

5.label: 5x06. 316
5.plot: The members of Oceanic 6 discover how to get back to the island, but not all of them want to return.

5.label: 5x07. The Life and Death of Jeremy Bentham
5.plot: Locke's mission off the island as Jeremy is revealed.
5.title: The Life and Death of Jeremy Bentham

5.label: 5x08. LaFleur
5.plot: Sawyer perpetuates a lie with some of the other island survivors in order to protect themselves from mistakes of the past.
5.title: LaFleur

5.label: 5x09. Namaste
5.plot: After meeting old acquaintances Sawyer is forced to continue lying to protect them.
5.title: Namaste

5.label: 5x10. He's Our You
5.plot: Everyone on the island is at risk when one of the survivors decides to go against them and taking matters into their own hands.
5.title: He's Our You

5.label: 5x11. Whatever Happened, Happened
5.plot: Kate goes to extreme measures to save Ben's life when Jack refuses to help. Meanwhile, Kate begins to tell the truth about the lie in order to protect Aaron.
5.title: Whatever Happened, Happened

5.label: 5x12. Dead Is Dead
5.plot: To atone for sins of the past, Ben must attempt to summon the smoke monster in order to be judged.
5.title: Dead Is Dead

5.label: 5x13. Some Like It Hoth
5.plot: Suspicions about a possible breach intensify after Ben is taken from the infirmary, and a reluctant Miles is forced to work with Hurley when he's asked to deliver an important package to a top Dharma official.
5.title: Some Like It Hoth

5.label: 5x05. This Place Is Death
5.plot: Locke shoulders the burden of ending the island's increasingly violent movements through time; Ben is stymied in his efforts to reunite the Oceanic 6 and bring them back to the island.
5.title: This Place Is Death

5.label: 5x13. Some Like It Hoth
5.plot: Suspicions about a possible breach intensify after Ben is taken from the infirmary, and a reluctant Miles is forced to work with Hurley when he's asked to deliver an important package to a top Dharma official.
5.title: Some Like It Hoth

5.label: 5x14. The Variable
5.plot: On the 100th episode milestone for the series, the time of reckoning has begun when Daniel Faraday comes clean regarding what he knows about the island.
5.title: The Variable

5.label: 5x15. Follow the Leader
5.plot: Jack and Kate find themselves at odds over the direction to take to save their fellow island survivors, Locke further solidifies his stance as leader of "The Others," and Sawyer and Juliet come under scrutiny from the Dharma Initiative.
5.title: Follow the Leader

5.label: 5x07. The Life and Death of Jeremy Bentham
5.plot: Locke's mission off the island as Jeremy is revealed.
5.title: The Life and Death of Jeremy Bentham

5.label: 5x16. The Incident (1)
5.plot: Jack's decision to put a plan in action in order to set things right on the island is met with some strong resistance by those close to him, and Locke assigns Ben a difficult task.
5.title: The Incident (1)

5.label: 5x17. The Incident (2)
5.plot: Jack's decision to put a plan in action in order to set things right on the island is met with some strong resistance by those close to him, and Locke assigns Ben a difficult task.
5.title: The Incident (2)

5.label: 5x01. Because You Left
5.plot: The remaining island survivors start to feel the effects of the aftermath of moving the island, and Jack and Ben begin their quest to reunite the Oceanic 6 in order to return to the island with Locke's body in an attempt to save their former fellow castaways.
5.title: Because You Left

5.label: 5x02. The Lie
5.plot: Hurley and Sayid are on the run from the cops after stumbling into trouble at the safehouse; the island survivors come under attack by unknown forces; and an old friend offers some shocking advice to Kate in order to ensure that "the lie" remain a secret.
5.title: The Lie

6.label: 6x01. LA X (1)
6.plot: A parallel universe, in which the crash never happened, is revealed as an aftermath of the bomb's detonation. Meanwhile, Sawyer blames Jack for the loss of Juliet and the true identity of the monster is revealed.
6.title: LA X (1)

6.label: 6x02. LA X (2)
6.plot: Jack, Sawyer, Kate, Miles and Hurley, struggling to save Sayid, face an ancient secret. Meanwhile, a fake Lock exits the chamber to everyone's awe.
6.title: LA X (2)

6.label: 6x03. What Kate Does
6.plot: Kate finds herself on the run, while Jack is tasked with something that could put a friend's life at risk.
6.title: What Kate Does

6.label: 6x04. The Substitute
6.plot: Locke goes in search of help to further his cause. Kate finds herself on the run, while Jack is tasked with something that could put a friend's life at risk.
6.title: The Substitute

6.label: 6x05. Lighthouse
6.plot: Hurley must convince Jack to accompany him on an unspecified mission, and Jin stumbles across an old friend.
6.title: Lighthouse

6.label: 6x06. Sundown
6.plot: Sayid is faced with a difficult decision, and Claire sends a warning to the temple inhabitants.
6.title: Sundown

6.label: 6x07. Dr. Linus
6.plot: Ben deals with the consequences of an uncovered lie.
6.title: Dr. Linus

6.label: 6x08. Recon
6.plot: Locke tasks Sawyer with a mission.
6.title: Recon

6.label: 6x09. Ab Aeterno
6.plot: Richard Alpert faces a difficult choice.
6.title: Ab Aeterno

6.label: 6x10. The Package
6.plot: Sun and Jin desperately continue their search for one another, and Locke confronts his enemy.
6.title: The Package

6.label: 6x11. Happily Ever After
6.plot: Desmond wakes up to discover he's back on the island.
6.title: Happily Ever After

6.label: 6x12. Everybody Loves Hugo
6.plot: Hurley worries about what the group should do next and Locke is curious about the new arrival in his camp.
6.title: Everybody Loves Hugo

6.label: 6x13. The Last Recruit
6.plot: Alliances are forged and broken as the Locke and Jack camps merge.
6.title: The Last Recruit

6.label: 6x14. The Candidate
6.plot: After the remaining survivors are reunited, Sawyer and Jack hatch a plan to divert the Man in Black's attention and leave the island without him on Widmore's submarine, but disastrous consequences await them. In the flash sideways, Jack investigates the cause of Locke's paralysis and offers treatment.
6.title: The Candidate

6.label: 6x15. Across the Sea
6.plot: The motives of John Locke are finally explained.
6.title: Across the Sea

6.label: 6x16. What They Died For
6.plot: While Locke devises a new strategy, Jack's group searches for Desmond.
6.title: What They Died For

6.label: 6x17. The End (1)
6.plot: Jack, the new protector of the island, meets with Locke and they go past the bamboo field with Desmond to visit the heart of the island. The Man in Black's final fate is determined, and one survivor must make the ultimate sacrifice to save the island. Meanwhile, in another life, the ones who might have been the survivors gather for a final time.
6.title: The End (1)

6.label: 6x18. The End (2)
6.plot: The Man in Black's final fate is determined, and one survivor must make the ultimate sacrifice to save the island. Meanwhile, in another life, the ones who might have been the survivors gather for a final time.
6.title: The End (2)
